sun.jvm.hotspot.debugger.cdbg

Interface ObjectVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultObjectVisitor

    public interface ObjectVisitor
    Provides uniform visitation to primitive and compound objects. Typically one will have an Address of an "object" (in the idealistic C++ definition, including "primitive objects" like ints) and a Type for that object. This visitor interface allows one to either get the value of the object (if of primitive type) or iterate through its fields, getting the value of each, in a consistent fashion. Also supports iteration through arrays of known length.
